r]]\n| 2000\u20132013\n| 63\n|}\n\n==Champions==\nBetween 1987\u20132002, the team at the top of the league was crowned English champions. From 2002\u201303, the winner of the league has been determined with a Premiership Final, which takes place at [[Twickenham Stadium|Twickenham]] and consists of two rounds of knock-out play amongst the top four teams.  Each season at least one team has been relegated at the end of the season, although occasionally teams are given a reprieve due to external factors e.g. promotion criteria.\n\n{| border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"3\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; font-size:92%; width:100%;\"\n|- style=\"background:blue;\"\n!style=\"color:white;\" \"width:21%;\"  |Season\n!style=\"color:white;\" \"width:21%;\" |Champions\n!style=\"color:white;\" \"width:6%;\" |Score\n!style=\"color:white;\" \"width:21%;\" |Runners-up\n!style=\"color:white;\" \"width:21%;\" |Relegated\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[1987\u201388 Courage League|1987\u2013<br>88]]\n|'''[[Leicester Tigers|Leicester]]'''\n| rowspan=15|N/A\n| [[Wasps RFC|Wasps]]\n| [[Sale Sharks|Sale]], [[Coventry R.F.C.|Coventry]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[1988\u201389 Courage League|1988\u2013<br>89]]\n|'''[[Bath Rugby|Bath]]'''\n| [[Gloucester Rugby|Gloucester]]\n| [[Liverpool St Helens F.C.|Liverpool St Helens]], [[Waterloo FC|Waterloo]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[1989\u201390 Courage League|1989\u2013<br>90]]\n|'''[[Wasps RFC|Wasps]]'''\n| [[Gloucester Rugby|Gloucester]]\n| [[Bedford Blues|Bedford]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[1990\u201391 English Premiership (rugby union)|1990\u2013<br>91]]\n|'''[[Bath Rugby|Bath]]'''\n| [[Wasps RFC|Wasps]]\n| [[Liverpool St Helens F.C.|Liverpool St Helens]], [[Birmingham Moseley Rugby Club|Moseley]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[1991\u201392 English Premiership (rugby union)|1991\u2013<br>92]]\n| '''[[Bath Rugby|Bath]]'''\n| [[Orrell RUFC|Orrell]]\n| [[Rosslyn Park F.C.|Rosslyn Park]], [[Nottingham RFC|Nottingham]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[1992\u201393 English Premiership (rugby union)|1992\u2013<br>93]]\n|'''[[Bath Rugby|Bath]]'''\n| [[Gloucester Rugby|Gloucester]]\n| [[Rugby Lions]], [[West Hartlepool R.F.C.|West Hartlepool]],<br>[[Saracen F.C.|Saracens]], [[London Scottish F.C.|London Scottish]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[1993\u201394 English Premiership (rugby union)|1993\u2013<br>94]]\n|'''[[Bath Rugby|Bath]]'''\n| [[Leicester Tigers|Leicester]]\n| [[Newcastle Falcons|Newcastle]], [[London Irish]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[1994\u201395 English Premiership (rugby union)|1994\u2013<br>95]]\n|'''[[Leicester Tigers|Leicester]]'''\n| [[Bath Rugby|Bath]]\n| [[Northampton Saints|Northampton]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[1995\u201396 English Premiership (rugby union)|1995\u2013<br>96]]\n|'''[[Bath Rugby|Bath]]'''\n| [[Leicester Tigers|Leicester]]\n| No relegation\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[1996\u201397 English Premiership (rugby union)|1996\u2013<br>97]]\n|'''[[Wasps RFC|Wasps]]'''\n| [[Bath Rugby|Bath]]\n| [[West Hartlepool R.F.C.|West Hartlepool]], [[Orrell R.U.F.C.|Orrell]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[1997\u201398 Premiership Rugby|1997\u2013<br>98]]\n|'''[[Newcastle Falcons|Newcastle]]'''\n| [[Saracens]]\n| [[Bristol Bears|Bristol]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[1998\u201399 Premiership Rugby|1998\u2013<br>99]]\n|'''[[Leicester Tigers|Leicester]]'''\n| [[Northampton Saints|Northampton]]\n| [[West Hartlepool R.F.C.|West Hartlepool]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[1999\u20132000 Premiership Rugby|1999\u2013<br>00]]\n|'''[[Leicester Tigers|Leicester]]'''\n| [[Bath Rugby|Bath]]\n| [[Bedford Blues|Bedford]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[2000\u201301 Premiership Rugby|2000\u2013<br>01]]\n|'''[[Leicester Tigers|Leicester]]'''\n| [[Wasps RFC|Wasps]]\n| [[Rotherham Titans|Rotherham]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[2001\u201302 Premiership Rugby|2001\u2013<br>02]]\n|'''[[Leicester Tigers|Leicester]]'''\n| [[Sale Sharks|Sale]]\n| No relegation\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[2002\u201303 Premiership Rugby|2002\u2013<br>03]]\n| '''[[Wasps RFC|Wasps]]'''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|'''39 \u2013 3'''\n| [[Gloucester Rugby|Gloucester]]\n| [[Bristol Bears|Bristol]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[2003\u201304 Premiership Rugby|2003\u2013<br>04]]\n| '''[[Wasps RFC|Wasps]]'''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|'''10 \u2013 6'''\n| [[Bath Rugby|Bath]]\n| [[Rotherham Titans|Rotherham]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[2004\u201305 Premiership Rugby|2004\u2013<br>05]]\n| '''[[Wasps RFC|Wasps]]'''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|'''39 \u2013 14'''\n| [[Leicester Tigers|Leicester]]\n| [[Harlequin F.C.|Harlequins]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[2005\u201306 Premiership Rugby|2005\u2013<br>06]]\n| '''[[Sale Sharks|Sale]]'''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|'''45 \u2013 20'''\n| [[Leicester Tigers|Leicester]]\n| [[Yorkshire Carnegie|Leeds Tykes]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[2006\u201307 Premiership Rugby|2006\u2013<br>07]]\n| '''[[Leicester Tigers|Leicester]]'''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|'''44 \u2013 16'''\n| [[Gloucester Rugby|Gloucester]]\n| [[Northampton Saints|Northampton]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[2007\u201308 Premiership Rugby|2007\u2013<br>08]]\n| '''[[Wasps RFC|Wasps]]'''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|'''26 \u2013 16'''\n| [[Leicester Tigers|Leicester]]\n| [[Yorkshire Carnegie|Leeds Carnegie]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[2008\u201309 Premiership Rugby|2008\u2013<br>09]]\n| '''[[Leicester Tigers|Leicester]]'''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|'''10 \u2013 9'''\n| [[London Irish]]\n| [[Bristol Bears|Bristol]]\n|- style=\"background:#f5faff;\"\n| [[2009\u201310 Premiership Rugby|2009\u2013<br>10]]\n| '''[[Leicester Tigers|Leicester]]'''\n| style=\"text-align: center;\"|'''33 \u2013 27'''\n| [[Saracens F.C.|Saracens]]\n| [[Worcester Warriors|