al stadium capacity\n\n{{reflist|group=f}}\n\n===All time===\n\nA total of 28 clubs have been involved in the top-flight since the league's inception in the 1987\u201388 season. The most recent club to make its debut in the Premiership was [[London Welsh RFC|London Welsh]], which made their top flight debut in 2012\u201313.\n\nFour clubs\u2014[[Bath Rugby|Bath]], [[Gloucester Rugby|Gloucester]], [[Leicester Tigers|Leicester]] and [[Wasps RFC|Wasps]]\u2014have appeared in every season to date. Harlequins have only missed the 2005\u201306 season.  Six other clubs have appeared in at least 20 seasons: Saracens, Northampton, Sale, London Irish, Bristol and Newcastle.\n\nCoventry, Liverpool St Helens, Moseley, Nottingham, Rosslyn Park, Rugby and Waterloo only appeared during the amateur era, whereas Exeter, Leeds, London Welsh, Richmond, Rotherham and Worcester have only appeared during the professional era.\n\nBelow, the 2019\u201320 clubs are listed in '''bold'''; ever-present clubs are listed in '''''bold italics'''''. Years listed are the calendar years in which the seasons ended.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! Seasons !! Team !!class=\"unsortable\"| Dates \n|-\n| '''''33''''' || '''''[[Bath Rugby|Bath]]''''' || 1988\u20132020\n|-\n| '''22''' || '''[[Bristol Bears|Bristol]]''' || 1988\u20131998, 2000\u20132003, 2006\u20132009, 2017, 2019\u20132020\n|-\n| 3 || [[Bedford Blues|Bedford]] || 1990, 1999\u20132000\n|-\n| 1 || [[Coventry R.F.C.|Coventry]] || 1988\n|-\n| '''10''' || '''[[Exeter Chiefs|Exeter]]''' || 2011\u20132020\n|-\n| '''''33''''' || '''''[[Gloucester Rugby|Gloucester]]''''' || 1988\u20132020\n|-\n| '''32''' || '''[[Harlequin F.C.|Harlequins]]''' || 1988\u20132005, 2007\u20132020\n|-\n| 8 || [[Yorkshire Carnegie|Leeds]]* || 2002\u20132006, 2008, 2010\u20132011\n|-\n| '''''33''''' || '''''[[Leicester Tigers|Leicester]]''''' || 1988\u20132020\n|-\n| 2 || [[Liverpool St Helens F.C.|Liverpool St Helens]] || 1989, 1991\n|-\n| 